    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>Allow users to login with either Email Address or Username.</p>\n<p>Just install the Plugin, no coding experience required.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<p>There is no setting for this plugin just install it and eveything will work automatically</p>\n<p>e.g.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Upload <code>/login-with-username-or-email/</code> to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the &#8216;Plugins&#8217; menu in WordPress</li>\n<li>Now you can use Email or username to log in</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "faq": "\n<h4>Will this plugin allow users to login using either their username or their email address?</h4>\n<p>\n<p>YES, the plugin allows either to be used in the login screen.</p>\n</p>\n\n",
